WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.762 --> 01:04.754
- But Professor...
- No. The answers are all there in the test.

02:16.173 --> 02:18.641
Aren't you forgetting something?

02:18.709 --> 02:22.874
I know. It's something to do with
the third differential coefficient.

02:22.948 --> 02:25.416
- Not that, Tonight,
- What?

02:25.484 --> 02:27.975
Emma?

02:28.053 --> 02:31.147
- What time is it?
- Almost5... 00,

02:31.223 --> 02:33.714
Oh, God.

02:42.535 --> 02:45.834
My proposal for utilizing
solar power, rejected,

02:45.905 --> 02:48.897
My concepts for harnessing
micro-energy waves, rejected,

02:48.975 --> 02:52.968
The dean suggests that
I focus on something that
might actually help mankind,

02:53.046 --> 02:55.105
Like his study on the benefits
of tobacco consumption,

02:55.181 --> 02:58.844
Alex, the problem is
your ideas are a bit too... radical,

02:58.918 --> 03:01.716
The problem is with
the faculty. They're dinosaurs.

03:01.788 --> 03:04.019
They're already extinct;
they just don't know it.

03:04.091 --> 03:08.118
They'll be discovered by some
future archaeologist, and he
won't know what to make of them.

03:08.195 --> 03:10.493
Their dim little eyes,
devoid of any curiosity...

03:10.564 --> 03:12.930
Alex, it's your first year
as associate professor.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.231
You might want to play things
a little more conservatively.

03:16.303 --> 03:18.703
You sound just like my father.

03:18.772 --> 03:22.572
Look at them, Philby. All alike.
All in identical bowler hats.

03:22.643 --> 03:24.874
Do you want your students
to turn out like that?

03:24.946 --> 03:28.814
I want my students prepared
for the realities of the world
they're about to greet.

03:28.883 --> 03:33.286
Well, I don't. I want them
to run along this street and
knock off every bowler they see.

03:36.291 --> 03:38.316
Mrs. Watchit!

03:38.393 --> 03:40.691
Oh, huzzah, the master's home.

03:40.762 --> 03:42.662
- Did you get it?
- Hello, Mr. Philby.

03:42.730 --> 03:45.392
Hello, Mrs. Watchit.
You're looking in the pink.

03:45.467 --> 03:48.869
Must be all the exercise I get
scampering up and down
these stairs like a wee lad.

03:48.938 --> 03:50.929
- Don't torture me. Did you get it?
- I got it.

03:51.006 --> 03:53.440
- Good. Let me see.
- But don't you think for one moment...

03:53.509 --> 03:56.171
I'm going to let you go out
in that filthy jacket.

03:56.245 --> 03:59.806
Now, go in there and change.

04:05.321 --> 04:09.190
And you've got another letter
from that annoying little man.

04:09.259 --> 04:12.660
Well, go ahead,
Switch it on,

04:12.729 --> 04:17.257
- It'll help people keep
their teeth well into their 40s,

04:17.334 --> 04:21.100
- You might think about
having that cleaned.
- Oh, who has the time?

04:21.171 --> 04:24.504
- How did you know with Molly?
- Know what?

04:24.574 --> 04:28.738
- You were meant to be together.
- She made the best
shepherd's pie I ever tasted.

04:28.812 --> 04:30.781
Don't you have a single
romantic bone in your body?

04:30.848 --> 04:34.716
No. I'm all bowler hat.

04:37.388 --> 04:40.721
Why do you waste your time
on that crackpot?

04:40.791 --> 04:43.259
Because he has some
very interesting ideas.

04:43.327 --> 04:47.286
A professor at Columbia
should not be corresponding
with a crazy German bookkeeper.

04:47.365 --> 04:49.526
He's a patent clerk,
not a bookkeeper.

04:49.600 --> 04:53.435
I think Mr. Einstein deserves
all the support I can give him.

04:53.505 --> 04:56.497
I wonder if we'll ever go too far?

04:56.575 --> 04:58.543
- With what?
- With this.

04:58.610 --> 05:01.670
With all of this.

05:01.747 --> 05:03.874
No such thing.

05:06.618 --> 05:09.178
All right. How do I look?

05:09.254 --> 05:12.155
Practically decent. Really, Alex.
Good luck tonight.

05:12.224 --> 05:15.388
She's a fine girl. She's done
wonderful things for you.

05:15.461 --> 05:19.261
Don't worry. You still have that
alluring smell of chalk.

05:19.332 --> 05:22.426
Oh, gotta hurry.

05:22.502 --> 05:26.666
Now, that's more like it.
You look a proper gentleman for once.

05:26.739 --> 05:29.264
Well, you better hope so. If Emma
turns me down, you'll be next.

05:29.342 --> 05:32.573
- Oh, I'm already swooning.

05:32.645 --> 05:35.979
All right. Wish me luck.

05:40.854 --> 05:42.788
Thank you.

05:50.831 --> 05:55.097
Fresh flowers. Fresh flowers.

05:59.107 --> 06:01.598
- Have some flowers, sir.
- Not tonight, thanks.

06:01.676 --> 06:04.975
No. I promised her flowers.

06:13.922 --> 06:15.856
Spectacular.

06:15.924 --> 06:19.759
Spectacular waste of money.
Damn thing's always breaking down.

06:19.829 --> 06:22.423
- Do you need a lift?
- Yes, yes.

06:22.498 --> 06:25.865
- How do you keep
the water temperature stable?
- There's a cantilevered gasket...

06:25.935 --> 06:28.233
- On the fuel regulator...

06:28.304 --> 06:31.330
Oh, God. Uh...

06:31.407 --> 06:35.400
Much obliged.
I'm always forgetting the damn brake.

06:35.478 --> 06:39.313
Hop in. I'll give you a perambulation
before it breaks down again.

06:39.383 --> 06:42.546
Oh, uh, I'm afraid
I have a prior engagement.

06:42.619 --> 06:45.281
Well, another time then.
We perambulate here most every night.

06:45.355 --> 06:47.016
Certainly.

06:49.526 --> 06:53.519
- Get a horse!

06:53.597 --> 06:55.588
Yes.

07:29.168 --> 07:31.398
Alexander?

07:39.211 --> 07:42.180
- Oh! Whoa.

07:42.247 --> 07:47.845
- You're late, Professor.
- I got here as soon as I could.

07:47.921 --> 07:52.358
Well, they say it's all the rage
in Paris. But I just picked it up...

07:52.425 --> 07:57.761
- Five dollars at Macy's.
Silly, isn't it?
- Very silly. I like it.

07:57.831 --> 08:01.426
Well, where are they?

08:01.501 --> 08:03.765
- What?
- The flowers.

08:03.837 --> 08:06.204
You promised me flowers tonight.
Don't you even remember?

08:06.273 --> 08:09.572
Oh, I'm sorry.
l... Well, I was distracted.

08:09.643 --> 08:11.975
Well, there's something new.

08:12.046 --> 08:15.675
- Uh, Emma, I need to talk to you.

08:23.190 --> 08:27.786
- Oh, uh, shall we walk through the park?
- Yes.

08:32.100 --> 08:36.092
Professor, you're shivering. I hope
you're not coming down with something.

08:38.006 --> 08:40.668
Well, I'm afraid I am.

08:40.741 --> 08:45.645
I'm not sleeping very well, and even
when I'm awake, I'm not much use.

08:45.714 --> 08:49.708
I can't eat or think
or do much of anything anymore.

08:51.888 --> 08:56.052
And the worst part is,
I don't know that I'll ever be well.

08:56.125 --> 09:00.653
I think there's only one remedy,
and that's for you to marry me...

09:00.730 --> 09:05.565
- And spend the rest
of your life with me.

09:08.171 --> 09:12.302
Oh, Emma, I know it's right.
I know we're meant to be together.

09:12.376 --> 09:16.472
It's the only thing in my entire life
I've never had to think about.

09:16.547 --> 09:18.640
Oh, Alex.

09:20.350 --> 09:23.251
Uh-Uh, wait.
I have something for you.

09:29.326 --> 09:33.491
You know, the moment is rather dying here.

09:33.565 --> 09:36.398
l-I know.
Hold on. Oh.

09:47.111 --> 09:50.444
- I know it's not a diamond.
- A moonstone.

09:50.515 --> 09:53.484
Well, it's your birthstone.
I thought...

09:53.551 --> 09:56.385
You thought right.

10:06.765 --> 10:10.257
I just might cry,

10:10.336 --> 10:14.329
I couldn't help but overhear.

10:14.406 --> 10:20.243
Two fine young people starting out
on the road of life.

10:20.313 --> 10:22.679
- I wish you the very best.

10:22.749 --> 10:26.310
- Well, thank you.
- And as much as I hate to do this...

10:26.386 --> 10:31.050
moved as I am by your...
protestations of love...

10:31.124 --> 10:34.389
I'll be needing
your money now.

10:34.461 --> 10:37.589
- Sir?
- And your jewellery too.

10:37.664 --> 10:42.261
I guess we could call this
your first little bump
on the road to marital bliss.

10:42.336 --> 10:45.999
- I don't understand...
- Don't make a scene.
There's no cause for that.

10:46.073 --> 10:49.406
- Just give me your wallet, will you?
- Hmm?

10:50.978 --> 10:52.912
Did you hear me, lad?

10:52.980 --> 10:56.848
Uh, all right, all right.
Here. That's everything.

10:58.686 --> 11:01.155
And your watch.

11:04.593 --> 11:07.289
And the gloves.

11:12.234 --> 11:16.193
- And the ring.
- No.

11:16.271 --> 11:19.206
I'm afraid so, darling.

11:19.274 --> 11:24.372
- And maybe he'll
buy you a diamond now.
- Please, please. Not that.

11:24.447 --> 11:26.972
Don't!

11:36.559 --> 11:41.258
Why did you do that?
It's only a ring.

11:46.070 --> 11:47.765
Emma?

11:56.246 --> 11:59.409
Emma?

11:59.483 --> 12:02.475
Oh!

12:39.225 --> 12:42.888
- What?

12:49.703 --> 12:55.369
Oh. Oh, sir,
Mr. Philby's here.

12:55.442 --> 12:58.741
- Here?
- Yes, sir, He insisted on coming...

12:58.812 --> 13:03.306
- Tell him to go away, I'm busy,
- I won't go away, Alex.

13:04.985 --> 13:08.318
My God.
What's happened to you?

13:10.224 --> 13:13.022
I've been...
I've been working.

13:13.094 --> 13:16.757
You remember that?
You used to care about your work.

13:16.831 --> 13:20.494
I care more about my life.
And yours.

13:20.568 --> 13:23.059
I came by the house every day
after the funeral...

13:23.137 --> 13:26.038
and every week
and every other month.

13:26.107 --> 13:30.271
Then I stopped coming.
Did you even notice?

13:30.344 --> 13:35.078
- It hurt me, Alex... very much.
- Then why are you here now?

13:35.150 --> 13:38.608
- There are some things I have to
say you may not like hearing...
- I know. I know.

13:38.687 --> 13:42.646
You're concerned. I know.
I hear it from Mrs. Watchit every day.

13:42.725 --> 13:46.422
But really...
I need you to go.

13:46.495 --> 13:49.328
- I won't leave. Not with
you hiding down here.
- I'm not hiding.

13:49.398 --> 13:52.890
You know that's what it is.
Mrs. Watchit says you're in
here all hours... day and night.

13:52.968 --> 13:55.802
Alex, will you please
stand still and look at me!

13:59.109 --> 14:02.806
It wasn't your fault.

14:04.948 --> 14:09.783
No. It wasn't my fault.

14:09.853 --> 14:15.417
Maybe we should blame Mrs. Watchit for
picking up the ring from the jeweller.

14:15.493 --> 14:18.758
Or the jeweller for making it.

14:18.829 --> 14:23.823
Or the poor bastard who tore
the stone from the earth.

14:23.901 --> 14:28.270
Maybe I should blame you
for introducing me to Emma
in the first place. Yes.

14:28.339 --> 14:33.106
Alexander, nothing will
ever change what happened.

14:33.177 --> 14:38.514
No, you're wrong,
because I will change it.

14:38.583 --> 14:42.747
David, I appreciate
your concern. I do.

14:42.821 --> 14:45.949
But I ask you to have faith in me.

14:46.024 --> 14:49.187
Well, l-I want to have
faith in you, Alex, but...

14:49.261 --> 14:53.493
Wha... What are...
What are you doing here?

14:53.565 --> 14:58.559
I'll tell you what.
Why don't you come by for dinner
in a week, and I'll show you?

14:58.637 --> 15:03.007
- Why don't you come home
with me now? Molly...
- Did you not hear me, David?

15:04.811 --> 15:07.780
I can't leave
when I'm so close.

15:10.183 --> 15:13.516
All right. We'll continue
this conversation in a week.

15:19.425 --> 15:22.759
In a week, we'll never even
have had this conversation.

18:33.128 --> 18:36.292
Ah. Thank you, my good man.

19:00.857 --> 19:04.850
You're early.
That's a first.

19:04.928 --> 19:08.955
I wanted to see you.

19:09.032 --> 19:11.432
Well, where are they?

19:11.501 --> 19:15.904
- What?
- The flowers.

19:17.474 --> 19:20.808
You promised me flowers tonight.
Don't you even remember?

19:32.323 --> 19:36.555
You never cease
to surprise me.

19:41.433 --> 19:45.028
Emma, I need to talk to you.

19:45.104 --> 19:48.505
- Shall we walk through the park?
- No!

19:48.574 --> 19:50.940
No,

19:52.644 --> 19:56.444
No. Let's go into the city.

19:56.515 --> 19:59.177
- Alex, what is it?
- Nothing. Let's just hurry.

19:59.251 --> 20:04.212
Running along is all very well for you.
You're not wearing a corset.

20:08.361 --> 20:11.353
- Bleecker Street, and be quick about it.

20:35.990 --> 20:38.481
Now you're all gallant.

20:46.268 --> 20:51.069
Professor, you're shivering. I hope
you're not coming down with something.

20:51.139 --> 20:55.701
No, no. I'm fine.

20:55.777 --> 21:00.544
I'm wonderful. I'm walking down
the street with you again.

21:00.615 --> 21:03.448
But we took a walk
three days ago.

21:03.518 --> 21:08.218
Well, not like this.
Never like this.

21:08.291 --> 21:12.728
- Heavens, look at that car.
- Oh, I've seen it.

21:12.795 --> 21:17.664
Now I know you're ill. You're passing up
the chance to explore some new gadget.

21:17.733 --> 21:22.568
- It's only a machine.
- Alexander, tell me what's going on.

21:22.638 --> 21:26.506
- Is something wrong?
- No.

21:26.576 --> 21:29.568
No.
Emma, listen to me.

21:29.646 --> 21:33.047
I need to leave you now, but I want you
to go straight home and stay there.

21:33.116 --> 21:37.951
I promise you I'll come by
sometime later tonight,
and I won't make any sense.

21:38.021 --> 21:41.354
I'll be all upset that you didn't meet
me in the park, but you must trust me.

21:41.425 --> 21:44.417
Everything will be all right.

21:45.929 --> 21:50.730
Just know how much I love you,
how much I'll always love you.

21:56.507 --> 21:59.999
All right.

22:00.078 --> 22:03.514
But first, where are my flowers?

22:08.553 --> 22:12.284
- Flowers it is.

22:12.357 --> 22:14.690
Wait right there.
Don't move.

22:24.637 --> 22:28.095
- Oh, can I help you, sir?
- Yes, a dozen roses. White.

22:28.173 --> 22:30.107
- No, no. Red.
- Look out!

22:50.930 --> 22:55.264
- Easy. Easy.

23:17.792 --> 23:21.285
I'm looking for
Professor Hartdegen.

23:28.103 --> 23:32.267
Alex, I'm...
I'm so sorry.

23:33.642 --> 23:37.772
- This was not supposed to happen.
- Of course not.

23:39.715 --> 23:43.709
- I know there's nothing I can say.
- We were out of the park, Philby.

23:43.786 --> 23:46.118
We were safe.

23:48.925 --> 23:51.917
Why can't I change it?

23:55.565 --> 23:58.898
I could come back
a thousand times.

23:58.968 --> 24:01.961
See her die a thousand ways.

24:04.241 --> 24:07.438
I don't...
I don't understand.

24:07.511 --> 24:10.844
I can't find the answer here.

24:12.716 --> 24:15.207
Not here.

24:21.525 --> 24:24.188
Not now.

27:47.307 --> 27:51.175
The future is now.

27:51.244 --> 27:54.111
Certain restrictions apply.
Blackout periods on availability
subject to change.

27:54.181 --> 27:58.709
